crossCuttingThemes[5]{id,name,severity,flaggedBy,description}:
  CC-01,Phase 5 / Phase 11 coupling,blocking,"strategy,phasing,agentic-workflow",Phase 5 (W2) writes documentation that references snapshot helper but the helper lives in Phase 11 (W4). Phase 5's M-01 gate is untestable until Phase 11 ships. Fix: promote Phase 11 to W2 (after Phase 5) OR split Phase 5 ACs into doc-only + post-Phase-11 tiers.
  CC-02,library.yaml double-write,blocking,"parallelization,feature-coverage",Phase 10 AC says it updates library.yaml but Phase 12 is the sole declared owner. Will clobber. Fix: remove library.yaml line from Phase 10; defer entirely to Phase 12.
  CC-03,Phase 9 underspecification,warning,"phasing,parallelization,agentic-workflow",TS spawn mechanism not specified; loom-converge.md and reviewer agents not in files-in; AgentResult-to-ConvergenceFindings severity mapping missing; Phase 2 dep is reversed causality. Phase 9 is the largest TS implementation in the plan; under-spec creates highest implementation risk.
  CC-04,create.md cross-wave conflict,warning,"parallelization,agentic-workflow",Phase 7 (W3) and Phase 10 (W4) both modify create.md in disjoint sections but no inter-wave grep gate or starting-state protocol. Phase 10 agent could clobber Step 1.7 if given pre-Phase-7 file as input.
  CC-05,W3 mislabeled as parallel,info,"phasing,parallelization",Phases 6→7→8 form a serial chain in W3 due to declared dependencies. Should be relabeled W3a (6+8 parallel) → W3b (7 after 6 merges) for executor clarity.

